1. The Core Workflow (5 Steps)

STEP 1 — Open the Repo

You open the Legal‑Calculus repository yourself.
Copilot cannot access GitHub directly.

STEP 2 — Bring Content Into Copilot

Choose one:

- Copy/paste text from a repo file
• Upload the file into Copilot

This is the only way Copilot can work with repo content.

STEP 3 — Think With Copilot Pro

Once the content is pasted, Copilot can help you:

- analyze
• rewrite
• structure
• build modules
• stress‑test arguments
• generate Blueprint AI workflows

Copilot Pro is the thinking engine of the system.

STEP 4 — You Decide

You review the output and choose what belongs in the record.
This preserves human control and procedural integrity.

STEP 5 — Commit to GitHub

You paste the improved content back into the repo and commit it.
The repo becomes the living archive of Legal‑Calculus.

